The Passion According to Andrei
Part One

21
00:02:41,257 --> 00:02:43,282
- Pull the rope.
- This one?

22
00:02:49,365 --> 00:02:52,732
- Arkhip, give me the strap.
- Hold it.

23
00:02:56,706 --> 00:02:57,832
Take it.

24
00:02:59,942 --> 00:03:00,931
Look!

25
00:03:01,911 --> 00:03:03,071
It's Yefim, isn't it?

26
00:03:25,101 --> 00:03:27,331
- Come here and help.
- Pull the rope.

27
00:03:27,403 --> 00:03:29,803
- Hold on a second.
- Come on, quick!

28
00:03:31,808 --> 00:03:33,639
Where is it?

29
00:03:33,710 --> 00:03:36,508
- Where is it?
- Here.

30
00:03:40,216 --> 00:03:41,410
Come on, fast.

31
00:03:44,554 --> 00:03:47,182
Lift it.

32
00:04:06,709 --> 00:04:09,337
Lord. Let it go right.

33
00:04:14,517 --> 00:04:16,508
Untie it now.

34
00:04:16,652 --> 00:04:18,279
The rope is tangled.

35
00:04:18,354 --> 00:04:21,016
Hold it!

36
00:04:21,124 --> 00:04:22,853
We won't have enough time.

37
00:04:26,829 --> 00:04:28,023
I'm ready!

38
00:04:28,131 --> 00:04:30,190
Archipushka! You try to hold them!

39
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:32,757
Just a second.

40
00:04:34,804 --> 00:04:36,829
Come on!

41
00:04:36,906 --> 00:04:38,806
Hold him, hold him!

42
00:04:51,287 --> 00:04:54,154
I'm here. I'm here.

43
00:05:00,196 --> 00:05:01,561
Cut the rope, man!

44
00:05:01,631 --> 00:05:05,590
Cut the rope!

45
00:05:05,668 --> 00:05:08,762
I'll show you, cut the rope!

46
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:31,248
My God!

47
00:05:32,028 --> 00:05:34,394
Yefim!

48
00:05:34,464 --> 00:05:38,059
- Where are you going?
- Archipushka!

49
00:05:38,434 --> 00:05:43,235
I'm flying! I'm flying!

50
00:06:08,064 --> 00:06:13,502
Hey! Chase me! Chase me!

51
00:06:48,671 --> 00:06:50,502
My God! What is it?

52
00:07:12,061 --> 00:07:15,189
Archipushka!

53
00:08:14,824 --> 00:08:20,888
THE JESTER
Summer 1 400

54
00:08:34,610 --> 00:08:36,407
Danil!

55
00:08:39,548 --> 00:08:40,913
Danil!

56
00:08:42,918 --> 00:08:45,443
Danil! The Father
told you to go back!

57
00:08:47,123 --> 00:08:49,683
There is no one to paint the icons.

58
00:08:49,992 --> 00:08:51,186
For God's sake!

59
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:53,592
It's no business of yours.

60
00:08:53,663 --> 00:08:57,064
You will be sorry for that. You
will come begging on your knees.

61
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:58,600
But the Father will not forgive you.

62
00:08:58,668 --> 00:09:01,159
Come on. You never know.

63
00:09:01,237 --> 00:09:03,637
We shall see.

64
00:09:08,678 --> 00:09:10,669
It's not good.

65
00:09:10,746 --> 00:09:11,770
What?

66
00:09:12,181 --> 00:09:14,445
That we are leaving Troitsa.

67
00:09:23,726 --> 00:09:25,785
It's a shame.

68
00:09:27,797 --> 00:09:31,927
Aren't there enough painters
in Moscow without us, Danil?

69
00:09:32,835 --> 00:09:35,497
We'll find some sort of work.

70
00:09:35,571 --> 00:09:38,472
All this is right, but it's a pity that...

71
00:09:39,408 --> 00:09:42,969
I passed this birch every
day and never noticed it.

72
00:09:43,112 --> 00:09:47,310
When you know you'll never
see it again, it means something.

73
00:09:47,883 --> 00:09:52,217
It's been ten years. Nine
for you, but ten for me.

74
00:09:52,455 --> 00:09:54,514
No, seven for me, nine for you.

75
00:09:55,925 --> 00:09:58,291
- It's raining.
- Come on here.

76
00:09:58,394 --> 00:10:00,362
Let's go. We will not melt.

77
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:41,559
The jesters were walking.
Drunk on mead and beer...

78
00:10:41,771 --> 00:10:45,969
...when they met their
master, the Boyar...

79
00:10:46,142 --> 00:10:48,303
...and they sang, to greet him:

80
00:10:48,644 --> 00:10:52,136
O master. O Boyar...

81
00:10:52,248 --> 00:10:56,048
...everything is ready in the kitchen!

82
00:10:56,318 --> 00:11:01,881
The Boyar's plump
wife is a choosy trollop.

83
00:11:03,459 --> 00:11:07,418
Mistress, open the door.
The master's coming!

84
00:11:08,097 --> 00:11:12,693
The Boyar yells: "Jesters are
all thieves and drunkards!

85
00:11:13,702 --> 00:11:17,035
"You should be whipped
from Friday to Friday!"

86
00:11:17,273 --> 00:11:21,232
"You goats and tramps,
drown in your beer!

87
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:24,340
"Soon you will be impaled!"

88
00:11:24,713 --> 00:11:28,911
The Jesters grabbed him
between his navel and his knees.

89
00:11:32,488 --> 00:11:37,084
They shaved his beard; what's
a Boyar without his beard?

90
00:11:37,359 --> 00:11:41,420
Any woman would
rather he had a beard.

91
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:46,192
The Boyar yells,
hops about like a flea.

92
00:11:46,569 --> 00:11:50,505
He scurries home,
raps on the window.

93
00:11:54,210 --> 00:11:58,738
But his wife doesn't
recognize his naked cheeks...

94
00:12:00,482 --> 00:12:03,883
...with no beard to grab hold of.

95
00:12:04,153 --> 00:12:07,520
She whacked him with a rolling pin.

96
00:12:08,924 --> 00:12:10,721
What a disgrace!

97
00:12:12,761 --> 00:12:16,253
"Cover your naked cheeks
with your breeches.

98
00:12:16,799 --> 00:12:19,529
"Clear off, beardless Boyar!"

99
00:12:21,403 --> 00:12:25,430
He hobbled off, pursued by geese...

100
00:12:25,641 --> 00:12:28,371
...and met a priest...

101
00:12:28,711 --> 00:12:34,274
...who mistook him for a woman and
dragged him into the bushes.

102
00:12:36,819 --> 00:12:39,845
Without breeches...

103
00:12:40,189 --> 00:12:44,250
...he looks the same at each end.

104
00:13:13,389 --> 00:13:16,483
The woman saw a naked head...

105
00:13:16,992 --> 00:13:20,359
...and grabbed it by the beard.

106
00:13:31,941 --> 00:13:35,707
May we shelter from the storm?

107
00:13:36,445 --> 00:13:38,174
Come in.

108
00:13:44,453 --> 00:13:47,684
Do you want some beer?
You are soaking wet.

109
00:13:47,756 --> 00:13:49,383
Thank you, we don't imbibe.

110
00:13:49,725 --> 00:13:51,215
And don't play around with women.

111
00:15:49,445 --> 00:15:52,414
God sent priests, but
the devil sent jesters.

112
00:16:33,455 --> 00:16:35,047
The woman saw a head!

113
00:16:37,126 --> 00:16:38,650
By the beard!

114
00:16:55,043 --> 00:16:58,843
My woman might have
been playing in the bushes.

115
00:17:04,987 --> 00:17:06,454
I'll show you!

116
00:18:22,531 --> 00:18:24,863
Come here, you.

117
00:18:54,696 --> 00:18:55,924
What are you doing?

118
00:19:30,966 --> 00:19:32,263
Give it back to him.

119
00:19:50,886 --> 00:19:52,581
Where were you, Kirill?

120
00:19:52,821 --> 00:19:55,415
Outside. Shall we go?

121
00:20:04,499 --> 00:20:10,062
Danil, the rain's stopped; let's go.

122
00:20:39,701 --> 00:20:41,532
Christ be with you, mistress.

123
00:21:38,994 --> 00:21:45,832
THEOPH ANES THE GREEK
Summer-Winter-Spring-Summer
1 405-1 406

124
00:21:55,243 --> 00:21:58,144
I'm innocent!

125
00:22:07,689 --> 00:22:08,713
Let me go!

126
00:22:43,391 --> 00:22:45,382
Is anyone in here?

127
00:23:22,330 --> 00:23:24,059
Have you come to look?

128
00:23:25,734 --> 00:23:26,723
Yes, to look.

129
00:23:34,042 --> 00:23:37,637
Then look. We'll soon be finished.

130
00:23:40,315 --> 00:23:43,716
So you are Theophanes the Greek?

131
00:23:47,689 --> 00:23:50,658
Why look at me? Look there.

132
00:23:52,294 --> 00:23:54,023
Where are you from?

133
00:23:54,396 --> 00:23:56,660
From Andronnikov Monastery.

134
00:23:57,165 --> 00:24:00,293
From Andronnikov Monastery?
Are you by chance Andrei Rublev?

135
00:24:03,371 --> 00:24:04,463
No.

136
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:08,976
I've heard everyone
praise this Rublev.

137
00:24:11,279 --> 00:24:15,340
He's good, but not as good as this.

138
00:24:19,521 --> 00:24:21,751
Such delicate colors.

139
00:24:26,361 --> 00:24:28,192
Oh Lord, it's just...

140
00:24:38,006 --> 00:24:41,908
Why did you stop
praising me? Go on.

141
00:24:41,977 --> 00:24:45,413
I can't. I can't find the right words.

142
00:24:45,614 --> 00:24:49,744
Konstantin Kostechevsky
was right when he said:

143
00:24:50,018 --> 00:24:52,543
"Only with true insight...

144
00:24:52,621 --> 00:24:55,089
"...can you grasp its essence."

145
00:24:57,359 --> 00:25:01,955
Whereas Andrei... and
I'll tell him to his face...

146
00:25:03,632 --> 00:25:06,533
He's like my brother.

147
00:25:07,002 --> 00:25:13,407
He's praised, it's true:
he paints well. With subtlety.

148
00:25:15,810 --> 00:25:19,644
But there's something
lacking in all his work.

149
00:25:23,952 --> 00:25:27,251
There's no awe, no faith...

150
00:25:27,956 --> 00:25:31,050
...no faith that comes from
the depths of his soul.

151
00:25:32,594 --> 00:25:34,255
No simplicity.

152
00:25:35,296 --> 00:25:41,292
As Epiphanius said in
"The Life of Saint Sergeius":

153
00:25:41,936 --> 00:25:44,029
"Simplicity, without gaudiness."

154
00:25:46,141 --> 00:25:49,770
That is what this is. It's sacred.

155
00:25:50,245 --> 00:25:55,239
Simplicity, without gaudiness...
you can't say it better.

156
00:25:55,316 --> 00:25:57,147
I see you are a wise man.

157
00:25:57,585 --> 00:25:59,849
If so, is that a good thing?

158
00:25:59,954 --> 00:26:05,290
If one is ignorant, isn't it better
to be guided by one's heart?

159
00:26:05,927 --> 00:26:08,953
In much wisdom
there is much grief...

160
00:26:09,698 --> 00:26:13,794
...and he who increases
knowledge increases sorrow.

161
00:26:20,341 --> 00:26:23,674
Proshka! Where is that oil?

162
00:26:24,045 --> 00:26:26,104
Whose ears should I box?

163
00:26:27,415 --> 00:26:29,542
It is as though the earth
has swallowed everyone.

164
00:26:29,617 --> 00:26:31,107
They say you paint quickly.

165
00:26:31,186 --> 00:26:34,417
I cannot work any
other way. I get bored.

166
00:26:35,023 --> 00:26:37,617
I wasted a week on an icon once.

167
00:26:37,792 --> 00:26:38,986
You threw it away?

168
00:26:39,728 --> 00:26:43,186
No. I used the board
to press cabbage.

169
00:26:43,498 --> 00:26:46,467
It's all so boring.

170
00:26:46,968 --> 00:26:49,459
I have pupils and
assistants in abundance...

171
00:26:49,537 --> 00:26:50,731
...but none of them is any good.

172
00:26:50,805 --> 00:26:53,205
They can neither read nor write.

173
00:26:55,744 --> 00:26:58,975
Listen, help me. Be my assistant.

174
00:27:01,382 --> 00:27:03,441
Don't make fun of me.

175
00:27:03,518 --> 00:27:05,383
I'm not making fun of you.

176
00:27:05,553 --> 00:27:10,354
In spring, I must paint the Church
of the Annunciation in Moscow...

177
00:27:10,425 --> 00:27:12,017
...and I have no
assistants to do it with.

178
00:27:12,093 --> 00:27:14,357
The scaffolding is being built.

179
00:27:14,529 --> 00:27:16,861
- Do you understand?
- I do understand.

180
00:27:16,931 --> 00:27:18,330
But I wouldn't be able to cope.

181
00:27:18,399 --> 00:27:23,200
I'll teach you. You never
prepared a wall for a fresco?

182
00:27:23,505 --> 00:27:28,306
You've a brain; even these
idiots can prepare a wall.

183
00:27:29,611 --> 00:27:31,738
I said no and I mean no.

184
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:33,811
You know best...

185
00:27:34,649 --> 00:27:39,211
...but mind you don't
regret it; I am rancorous.

186
00:27:39,487 --> 00:27:42,354
I may regret it, but it's a sin for you.

187
00:27:42,624 --> 00:27:45,855
An unknown monk comes to you...

188
00:27:46,528 --> 00:27:49,019
...and you like the fact that you
can talk about books with him...

189
00:27:49,097 --> 00:27:50,826
...and you decide to
take him and favor him.

190
00:27:52,066 --> 00:27:56,765
But I haven't looked at a book for
three years and I don't want to.

191
00:27:57,071 --> 00:28:00,040
- Why?
- I have a different road.

192
00:28:00,809 --> 00:28:03,972
Wicked bastards!

193
00:28:04,312 --> 00:28:06,303
Where is Proshka? Where is Vikenty?

194
00:28:06,381 --> 00:28:09,908
They ran to the square to see how
they were going to kill the ruler.

195
00:28:09,984 --> 00:28:13,249
Wicked bastards!

196
00:28:23,464 --> 00:28:25,193
See?

197
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:28,494
And you don't want to help?

198
00:28:39,347 --> 00:28:42,111
- I shall die soon.
- You shouldn't say that.

199
00:28:42,684 --> 00:28:47,314
The other night I
dreamed of an angel.

200
00:28:47,689 --> 00:28:50,123
He said: "Come with me."

201
00:28:50,959 --> 00:28:54,258
I said: " I shall die soon, without you."

202
00:29:08,743 --> 00:29:10,802
You won't change
your mind, will you?

203
00:29:13,181 --> 00:29:17,083
Only on one condition.

204
00:29:17,585 --> 00:29:20,645
Whatever you want.
Money? Half my fee, okay?

205
00:29:21,256 --> 00:29:25,920
No. I'll work for nothing
if you yourself...

206
00:29:28,029 --> 00:29:31,226
...come to Andronnikov
Monastery to fetch me.

207
00:29:31,933 --> 00:29:37,166
Before the community, the
metropolitan, ask me to help you...

208
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:42,406
...before the brotherhood,
before Andrei Rublev.

209
00:29:43,177 --> 00:29:45,805
Then I shall serve you like a slave...

210
00:29:46,414 --> 00:29:49,850
...like a dog, until the day I die.

211
00:29:50,218 --> 00:29:52,550
What is your name?

212
00:29:53,054 --> 00:29:54,282
Kirill.

213
00:30:02,797 --> 00:30:06,358
Orthodox Christians, lovers of truth.

214
00:30:06,834 --> 00:30:11,771
How long will this torture go
on, when will you end this?

215
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:15,999
You are thoughtless
sinners, yet you judge.

216
00:30:16,778 --> 00:30:20,771
You faithless heathens!

217
00:30:21,950 --> 00:30:23,850
He has already seven
times atoned for his sins...

218
00:30:23,918 --> 00:30:25,078
...for both his sins and yours.

219
00:30:25,153 --> 00:30:28,145
You are incredible
sinners yourselves.

220
00:30:28,222 --> 00:30:30,019
And you judge...

221
00:30:30,091 --> 00:30:32,616
...but you don't have God with you.

222
00:31:10,932 --> 00:31:14,129
Rejoice, O young man, in thy youth...

223
00:31:14,469 --> 00:31:19,065
...and let thy heart cheer thee
in the days of thy youth.

224
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:23,342
Walk in the ways of thine heart,
and in the sight of thine eyes...

225
00:31:23,511 --> 00:31:26,776
...but know that for all these...

226
00:31:27,015 --> 00:31:30,041
...God will bring thee into judgment.

227
00:31:41,195 --> 00:31:44,096
Remember now thy Creator
in the days of thy youth...

228
00:31:44,165 --> 00:31:45,757
...before the difficult days come...

229
00:31:46,034 --> 00:31:49,162
...and the years draw nigh,
when thou shalt say...

230
00:31:49,404 --> 00:31:52,498
..."I have no pleasure in them."

231
00:31:53,741 --> 00:31:54,730
Remember thy Creator...

232
00:31:54,809 --> 00:31:57,710
...before the silver cord be loosed.
Or the golden bowl be broken...

233
00:31:57,945 --> 00:32:00,778
...or the pitcher
shattered at the fountain...

234
00:32:01,049 --> 00:32:03,984
...or the wheel broken at the well.

235
00:32:05,286 --> 00:32:08,847
Then shall the dust return
to the earth as it was...

236
00:32:09,157 --> 00:32:12,183
...and the spirit shall return
unto God who gave it.

237
00:32:12,927 --> 00:32:17,261
"Vanity of vanities,"
saith the preacher; "All is vanity."

238
00:32:21,469 --> 00:32:23,869
Kirill, have you seen Father Nikodim?

239
00:32:26,641 --> 00:32:30,042
Where has he got to
since this morning?

240
00:32:30,411 --> 00:32:34,973
He took my gloves, then disappeared
as though the earth swallowed him.

241
00:32:37,652 --> 00:32:41,281
I have to chop wood
and the logs are icy.

242
00:32:44,525 --> 00:32:48,655
Why is your candle
burning? It's daylight.

243
00:32:51,032 --> 00:32:53,398
Did you feed my dog?

244
00:32:54,335 --> 00:32:56,428
Did you ask me to?

245
00:33:02,110 --> 00:33:03,907
What's the matter with you?

246
00:33:12,553 --> 00:33:13,542
Go away.

247
00:33:15,590 --> 00:33:19,356
The words of the wise are like
goads, and the words of scholars...

248
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:22,520
...are like well-driven nails,
given by one Shepherd.

249
00:33:22,597 --> 00:33:26,624
And further, my son, you
should stay away from these.

250
00:33:26,968 --> 00:33:29,960
Of making many
books there is no end...

251
00:33:30,071 --> 00:33:33,006
...and much study is
wearisome to the flesh.

252
00:33:33,708 --> 00:33:36,006
Let us hear the conclusion
of the whole matter...

253
00:33:36,244 --> 00:33:38,269
Fear God and keep
His commandments...

254
00:33:38,346 --> 00:33:41,110
...for this is man's all.

255
00:33:41,749 --> 00:33:44,047
A messenger has come!

256
00:33:44,585 --> 00:33:47,918
Who has come? A messenger
from Moscow has come.

257
00:33:49,624 --> 00:33:51,819
A messenger has come
from the Grand Prince.

258
00:33:51,893 --> 00:33:54,054
- So?
- So so!

259
00:33:54,428 --> 00:33:57,158
A messenger from
Theophanes the Greek.

260
00:34:00,468 --> 00:34:03,631
The Grand Prince
orders you to Moscow...

261
00:34:03,771 --> 00:34:08,708
...to paint the Cathedral of the
Annunciation, with Theophanes.

262
00:34:14,549 --> 00:34:18,508
Is he really Andrei
Rublev, this fellow?

263
00:34:23,257 --> 00:34:26,454
Yes, he's Rublev... and I'm Kirill.

264
00:34:27,195 --> 00:34:31,564
Theophanes the Greek says
he wants you in Moscow...

265
00:34:31,999 --> 00:34:33,830
...and he wishes to see you.

266
00:34:34,835 --> 00:34:37,099
I thank Theophanes.

267
00:34:38,339 --> 00:34:39,363
Tell him...

268
00:34:42,276 --> 00:34:44,369
...that I'll come.

269
00:34:46,447 --> 00:34:47,607
I'll come.

270
00:34:50,451 --> 00:34:52,043
My head is splitting!

271
00:34:56,224 --> 00:34:58,055
Bring my horse here.

272
00:35:00,361 --> 00:35:01,851
What is wrong?

273
00:35:05,700 --> 00:35:11,332
Choose whichever helpers you
like and be ready tomorrow.

274
00:35:12,006 --> 00:35:14,440
Is there a blacksmith
here? If not, I'll fall off again.

275
00:35:14,809 --> 00:35:19,212
There is a smithy outside,
beyond the chapel.

276
00:35:19,413 --> 00:35:21,540
Farewell, God-fearing people!

277
00:35:27,054 --> 00:35:28,612
Semyon! Come here!

278
00:35:28,689 --> 00:35:30,520
Come here and help us!

279
00:35:30,591 --> 00:35:32,650
Why are you standing? Come here!

280
00:35:48,476 --> 00:35:51,411
Let's go today, shall we, Danil?

281
00:35:52,246 --> 00:35:58,116
Go quickly, before
Theophanes changes his mind.

282
00:35:59,020 --> 00:36:00,647
I'm not going.

283
00:36:01,989 --> 00:36:03,115
Why aren't you going?

284
00:36:05,993 --> 00:36:08,723
How can I manage without you?

285
00:36:09,463 --> 00:36:10,930
As best you can.

286
00:36:14,568 --> 00:36:16,160
I thought we'd go together.

287
00:36:16,771 --> 00:36:20,867
Why did you think for
me? I was not invited.

288
00:36:26,747 --> 00:36:28,612
I can't do it without you.

289
00:36:30,117 --> 00:36:35,145
You can; you agreed
to go without asking me.

290
00:36:36,157 --> 00:36:38,284
Theophanes simply beckoned.

291
00:36:40,828 --> 00:36:44,821
Don't grieve; you're
not the first, or the last.

292
00:36:45,933 --> 00:36:48,424
Even without you there's
plenty of work for me here.

293
00:36:56,610 --> 00:36:57,975
Thank God for it.

294
00:36:59,613 --> 00:37:02,343
Foma, Aleksei. Let's get ready.

295
00:37:03,517 --> 00:37:05,747
Piotr, you're coming with me.

296
00:37:31,879 --> 00:37:33,608
Did you forget something, Andrei?

297
00:37:36,083 --> 00:37:37,914
I came to say farewell.

298
00:37:40,121 --> 00:37:41,383
We've said farewell.

299
00:37:54,468 --> 00:37:56,868
I came to say farewell, but...

300
00:38:02,376 --> 00:38:05,174
It was hard for me before.

301
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:10,278
Then the devil created
enmity between us.

302
00:38:12,686 --> 00:38:14,085
I can't go away like this.

303
00:38:16,190 --> 00:38:18,385
I must make confession.

304
00:38:21,128 --> 00:38:22,527
Will you hear it?

305
00:38:31,338 --> 00:38:34,136
I cannot do anything, Danil...

306
00:38:36,777 --> 00:38:40,008
...after living so many years
together in the same cell.

307
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:47,553
Apart from you, I have no one.

308
00:38:50,691 --> 00:38:53,717
I see the world with your eyes.

309
00:38:56,163 --> 00:38:57,653
I hear it with your ears...

310
00:39:00,401 --> 00:39:01,868
...with your heart.

311
00:39:10,544 --> 00:39:13,377
I am happy for you, you old fool.

312
00:39:13,781 --> 00:39:16,944
If only you knew how happy.

313
00:39:19,119 --> 00:39:22,748
Go to Moscow. Paint;
I shall be proud of you.

314
00:39:24,158 --> 00:39:28,322
The devil tempted me the
other day too. Forgive me.

315
00:39:55,689 --> 00:39:58,055
I'll come back, Danil.

316
00:40:12,740 --> 00:40:15,368
Where are you going?
What about Vespers?

317
00:40:15,609 --> 00:40:17,770
I'll manage without you.

318
00:40:18,345 --> 00:40:20,472
What's wrong with you today, Kirill?

319
00:40:21,949 --> 00:40:25,248
I'm tired of lying. I'm going
back into the secular world.

320
00:40:28,789 --> 00:40:31,155
Why did we leave
the Trinity Monastery?

321
00:40:31,659 --> 00:40:34,856
Andrei, Danil, you are
not saying anything.

322
00:40:35,930 --> 00:40:39,058
Because the brothers valued
profit higher than faith.

323
00:40:40,067 --> 00:40:42,968
They forgot why they had
entered a monastery. And now?

324
00:40:43,704 --> 00:40:47,800
We sought to praise God with faith
and work, but what's happened?

325
00:40:48,075 --> 00:40:50,305
The monastery's become a bazaar.

326
00:40:50,844 --> 00:40:54,405
Servant of God, how many souls
did you trade in for monasticism?

327
00:40:54,481 --> 00:40:55,470
Twenty or thirty?

328
00:40:55,849 --> 00:40:59,250
And you ran after the
Father Superior, bargaining.

329
00:40:59,753 --> 00:41:04,781
For two meadows, or even one,
you bought eternal salvation.

330
00:41:05,793 --> 00:41:10,594
You don't need me to tell you,
but you prefer to keep quiet.

331
00:41:11,165 --> 00:41:15,932
Perhaps I would also tolerate all
this loathsomeness if I had talent.

332
00:41:16,804 --> 00:41:20,331
But what talent? Just a
slight ability to paint icons.

333
00:41:20,941 --> 00:41:24,741
God be praised that
He gave me no talent.

334
00:41:25,012 --> 00:41:30,143
I'm happy I'm untalented; I can
be honest and pure before God.

335
00:41:30,217 --> 00:41:31,912
You are taking sin upon your soul!

336
00:41:31,986 --> 00:41:34,682
I'll tell you something else, brothers.

337
00:41:35,122 --> 00:41:38,785
What do you want to tell us
that we don't know already?

338
00:41:39,259 --> 00:41:44,629
Do you know what happens to your
sort? Speak! I won't get offended!

339
00:41:44,698 --> 00:41:45,687
Well, I...

340
00:41:45,766 --> 00:41:48,291
Get out, you dog!

341
00:41:48,736 --> 00:41:53,696
Out of my sight, you serpent!
Rejoin the secular world, slanderer!

342
00:41:54,375 --> 00:41:55,637
Now do you see?

343
00:41:56,010 --> 00:41:56,999
Kirill!

344
00:41:58,812 --> 00:41:59,972
Kirill!

345
00:42:17,131 --> 00:42:21,591
It is written: " And Jesus
went into the temple of God...

346
00:42:21,835 --> 00:42:25,566
"...and cast out all them that
sold and bought in the temple...

347
00:42:26,040 --> 00:42:29,339
"...and overthrew the tables
of the money changers...

348
00:42:29,743 --> 00:42:31,870
"...and the seats of them
that sold doves.

349
00:42:32,212 --> 00:42:36,774
" And said unto them," it is written,
" My house shall be called...

350
00:42:37,051 --> 00:42:41,681
"...the house of prayer; but ye
have made it a den of thieves."

351
00:43:41,648 --> 00:43:44,116
For three years I was
cleaning brushes for Danil...

352
00:43:44,184 --> 00:43:45,515
...before he let me touch an icon.

353
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:48,215
And then only to clean it.

354
00:43:48,322 --> 00:43:49,516
Don't you trust me?

355
00:43:50,557 --> 00:43:53,082
You're always lying, Foma.

356
00:43:53,293 --> 00:43:57,525
Yesterday your robe was
sticky; where were you?

357
00:43:58,065 --> 00:43:59,191
At the beehive.

358
00:43:59,733 --> 00:44:02,793
But you said you
were at the monastery.

359
00:44:03,036 --> 00:44:05,027
Just look at yourself.

360
00:44:06,273 --> 00:44:09,140
Put mud or something
on your cheek...

361
00:44:09,676 --> 00:44:12,770
...or you will swell, like a hog.

362
00:44:13,514 --> 00:44:16,005
It's too late now, it's useless.

363
00:44:19,286 --> 00:44:21,516
You're constantly making up stories.

364
00:44:26,026 --> 00:44:28,654
I even think you have a disease.

365
00:44:29,096 --> 00:44:30,757
Me? What disease?

366
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:41,398
There is a disease where a
man lies without stopping.

367
00:44:49,917 --> 00:44:51,077
Look, Foma.

368
00:44:53,453 --> 00:44:54,750
Look, I say.

369
00:44:56,456 --> 00:44:59,687
What?

370
00:45:01,395 --> 00:45:05,058
You think you know everything so
I'm not going to teach you any more.

371
00:45:07,134 --> 00:45:08,761
Why should I learn?

372
00:45:08,969 --> 00:45:11,460
Anyway, I will have to spend
three years cleaning the brushes.

373
00:45:12,206 --> 00:45:14,231
I'm sick and tired of you, Foma.

374
00:45:14,374 --> 00:45:17,275
Go back to the monastery,
go wherever you want.

375
00:45:33,060 --> 00:45:35,119
I can't understand why
I took you as a pupil.

376
00:45:35,429 --> 00:45:38,364
You are always like that. First
you say one thing then another.

377
00:45:38,632 --> 00:45:42,193
You yourself told
Theophanes I was perceptive.

378
00:45:42,469 --> 00:45:46,565
You were different then;
you worked, you didn't lie.

379
00:45:50,911 --> 00:45:53,072
And do you know
what Theophanes said?

380
00:45:53,146 --> 00:45:54,841
" What does it matter
if he's perceptive?"

381
00:45:56,516 --> 00:45:58,245
Whatever Theophanes has said...

382
00:45:58,352 --> 00:46:00,377
...I can see blue colors
better than anyone else.

383
00:46:03,724 --> 00:46:07,751
You eat too much; how can you
paint with a bloated stomach?

384
00:46:08,095 --> 00:46:11,656
When your stomach's rumbling,
how can your mind work?

385
00:46:12,132 --> 00:46:14,896
The rumbling is the
only sound you hear.

386
00:46:17,137 --> 00:46:21,073
You're lucky, Foma. For
you, everything is simple.

387
00:46:21,141 --> 00:46:24,167
If you are not painting, you
are sleeping or fooling around.

388
00:46:25,245 --> 00:46:30,478
But only by prayer can
the soul transcend the flesh.

389
00:46:32,085 --> 00:46:34,918
Would you go to learn from
another teacher instead of me?

390
00:46:35,022 --> 00:46:37,684
Why not, if you tell me to go?

391
00:46:38,058 --> 00:46:40,618
Come on, come on. Don't be angry.

392
00:46:44,865 --> 00:46:45,854
What's that?

393
00:47:12,159 --> 00:47:16,095
So you've decided to put
the apostle on the left, Andrei.

394
00:47:20,634 --> 00:47:22,898
Did you take the glue off the fire?

395
00:47:23,003 --> 00:47:24,834
Did you take the glue off the fire?

396
00:47:32,612 --> 00:47:34,671
Perceptive is he?

397
00:47:36,183 --> 00:47:38,947
He should be beaten
every Saturday, like a dog.

398
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:02,329
You're obstinate, Andrei.

399
00:49:02,969 --> 00:49:06,735
How did you see so much? Everyone
else is thinking only of himself.

400
00:49:07,107 --> 00:49:08,802
I saw it, Theophanes.

401
00:49:09,176 --> 00:49:12,043
The women of Moscow
gave their hair to the Tatars.

402
00:49:12,312 --> 00:49:15,145
What else could the
poor creatures do?

403
00:49:15,582 --> 00:49:19,848
Better to lose their hair than
be tortured. Is that heroic?

404
00:49:20,020 --> 00:49:21,009
It is.

405
00:49:22,022 --> 00:49:27,619
It is true that Russian women
are humiliated and unhappy.

406
00:49:29,463 --> 00:49:30,794
It's not what I mean.

407
00:49:31,031 --> 00:49:35,229
Tell me honestly, are the
people ignorant or not?

408
00:49:36,603 --> 00:49:38,093
Well, are they?

409
00:49:38,338 --> 00:49:41,330
They're ignorant, but
whose fault is that?

410
00:49:41,608 --> 00:49:46,170
It's their own stupidity. Have you
never sinned through ignorance?

411
00:49:46,913 --> 00:49:47,845
Everyone has.

412
00:49:48,215 --> 00:49:51,844
And I have too. God forgive
us and make us better.

413
00:49:52,786 --> 00:49:54,413
Well, never mind.

414
00:49:55,155 --> 00:49:59,091
The Last Judgment is coming;
we'll burn like candles.

415
00:49:59,693 --> 00:50:02,093
Mark my words.

416
00:50:03,263 --> 00:50:07,632
Each will accuse the other of
his own sins, to defend himself.

417
00:50:08,802 --> 00:50:14,104
Theophanes, how can you paint with
such ideas, even accept praise?

418
00:50:15,876 --> 00:50:19,539
I have become a hermit
and lived in a cave.

419
00:50:20,147 --> 00:50:22,547
I serve God, not man.

420
00:50:23,650 --> 00:50:29,111
As regards praise, what is praised
today is abused tomorrow.

421
00:50:29,456 --> 00:50:32,823
They will forget you, me, everything.

422
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:35,851
All is vanity and ashes. Worse
things have been forgotten.

423
00:50:37,531 --> 00:50:42,059
Humanity has already committed
every stupidity and baseness...

424
00:50:42,903 --> 00:50:44,837
...and now it only repeats them.

425
00:50:45,906 --> 00:50:50,002
Everything is an eternal circle
and it repeats and repeats itself.

426
00:50:50,810 --> 00:50:54,871
If Jesus returned to earth,
they would crucify him again.

427
00:50:55,115 --> 00:50:57,709
Of course, if only
evil is remembered...

428
00:50:58,985 --> 00:51:01,317
...then you will never be
happy in the sight of God.

429
00:51:03,223 --> 00:51:05,384
Perhaps we must forget
some things; but not all.

430
00:51:07,694 --> 00:51:09,559
I don't know how to say it.

431
00:51:09,863 --> 00:51:12,491
Then be quiet and listen to me.

432
00:51:17,003 --> 00:51:19,733
You think that one can
only do good alone?

433
00:51:20,373 --> 00:51:23,831
Good. Remember
the New Testament.

434
00:51:25,512 --> 00:51:29,278
Jesus taught people in the temples...

435
00:51:30,050 --> 00:51:33,816
...so why did they
gather later? To kill him!

436
00:51:34,788 --> 00:51:37,313
"Crucify him!" they shouted.

437
00:51:38,458 --> 00:51:42,189
And the disciples? Judas
sold Him. Peter denied Him.

438
00:51:43,430 --> 00:51:46,763
They all ran away,
yet they were the best.

439
00:51:47,467 --> 00:51:49,196
But they repented.

440
00:51:49,703 --> 00:51:53,833
That was afterwards,
when it was too late.

441
00:51:56,476 --> 00:52:00,207
It's never too late to repent.

442
00:52:12,192 --> 00:52:14,524
Of course, people do evil.

443
00:52:14,594 --> 00:52:19,224
But you can not
blame them altogether.

444
00:52:19,532 --> 00:52:20,999
It's difficult...

445
00:52:21,735 --> 00:52:23,498
...and sinful, I think.

446
00:52:24,671 --> 00:52:28,903
Judas sold the Christ, and
remember who bought him.

447
00:52:29,342 --> 00:52:30,366
People.

448
00:52:31,411 --> 00:52:33,504
And who accused Jesus?

449
00:52:34,414 --> 00:52:36,678
The scribes and Pharisees...

450
00:52:37,017 --> 00:52:39,485
...they could not find witnesses,
however hard they tried.

451
00:52:40,854 --> 00:52:43,254
"Who will testify against this innocent?"

452
00:52:44,424 --> 00:52:46,551
Only later on they found the traitors.

453
00:52:46,626 --> 00:52:49,060
Two were found immediately.
Two, and not one.

454
00:52:50,563 --> 00:52:52,053
There were only two.

455
00:52:52,866 --> 00:52:57,428
The Pharisees were
masters of deceit, educated.

456
00:52:58,672 --> 00:53:01,505
They had studied to gain power...

457
00:53:01,574 --> 00:53:03,508
...to take advantage of
the people's ignorance.

458
00:53:05,312 --> 00:53:08,907
We must remind people more
often that they are people.

459
00:53:09,249 --> 00:53:13,208
Russians, of the same
blood, of the same land.

460
00:53:14,688 --> 00:53:16,747
Evil is everywhere.

461
00:53:16,823 --> 00:53:20,816
Someone will always sell
you for thirty pieces of silver.

462
00:53:21,995 --> 00:53:25,692
New misfortunes constantly
befall the peasant...

463
00:53:25,799 --> 00:53:30,099
...either Tatars three times an
autumn, or famine, or plague...

464
00:53:30,737 --> 00:53:34,298
...and he still keeps on
working, working, working...

465
00:53:34,374 --> 00:53:36,535
...meekly bearing his cross.

466
00:53:36,609 --> 00:53:40,477
He does not despair,
he is silent and patient.

467
00:53:40,980 --> 00:53:44,040
He only prays to God
for enough strength.

468
00:53:45,618 --> 00:53:49,145
How could God not
forgive him his ignorance?

469
00:53:50,390 --> 00:53:57,319
You know yourself. You're
tired and discouraged...

470
00:53:57,964 --> 00:53:59,056
...and suddenly...

471
00:53:59,265 --> 00:54:02,962
...in the crowd you
meet a human glance...

472
00:54:03,536 --> 00:54:07,734
...and everything's lighter,
as it is after Communion.

473
00:54:08,475 --> 00:54:09,965
Isn't it so?

474
00:54:12,979 --> 00:54:15,379
You just spoke of Jesus.

475
00:54:16,082 --> 00:54:21,816
Perhaps He was born and
crucified to reconcile God and man.

476
00:54:22,555 --> 00:54:25,217
Jesus came from God,
so He is all-powerful.

477
00:54:26,159 --> 00:54:30,926
And if He died on the cross,
it was predetermined...

478
00:54:31,664 --> 00:54:35,191
...and His crucifixion
and death were God's will.

479
00:54:35,402 --> 00:54:37,893
That would have aroused hatred
not in those who crucified Him...

480
00:54:37,971 --> 00:54:39,233
...but in those who loved Him...

481
00:54:39,339 --> 00:54:44,174
...if they had been near
Him at that moment...

482
00:54:45,578 --> 00:54:48,376
...because they loved
Him as a man only.

483
00:54:49,416 --> 00:54:52,317
But if He, of His own will, left them...

484
00:54:52,485 --> 00:54:56,785
...He displayed injustice,
or even cruelty.

485
00:54:57,957 --> 00:55:00,949
Maybe those who
crucified Him loved Him...

486
00:55:01,995 --> 00:55:05,396
...because they helped
in this divine plan.

487
00:56:26,646 --> 00:56:29,080
Do you understand
what you are saying?

488
00:56:30,183 --> 00:56:35,018
They'll exile you to the north,
man, to renovate the icons.

489
00:56:35,121 --> 00:56:40,184
Am I not right? You too
always say what you think.

490
00:56:40,360 --> 00:56:45,730
But I'm not a monk; I'm free.

491
00:57:01,847 --> 00:57:06,614
