492
00:57:22,401 --> 00:57:23,925
Sergei, over here!

493
00:57:24,837 --> 00:57:26,429
Light the fire.

494
00:57:28,074 --> 00:57:30,804
Foma, let's get some logs.

495
00:57:35,948 --> 00:57:38,007
Piotr has probably never seen...

496
00:57:38,084 --> 00:57:40,314
...either Assumption Cathedral
or Saint Dmitry Cathedral.

497
00:57:41,187 --> 00:57:46,420
Never mind, he will begin
working, and understand things.

498
00:57:47,793 --> 00:57:50,284
Foma! Where are you?

499
00:57:50,529 --> 00:57:52,588
We won't be on time.

500
00:57:53,032 --> 00:57:54,431
It's okay, we'll be there tomorrow.

501
00:57:54,700 --> 00:57:57,965
No. We'll never finish the Cathedral
of the Assumption by winter.

502
00:57:58,104 --> 00:57:59,435
It's almost June, Andrei.

503
00:58:09,382 --> 00:58:10,371
What is it?

504
00:58:11,384 --> 00:58:13,852
Quiet! Do you hear it?

505
00:58:17,623 --> 00:58:18,885
Nightingales?

506
00:58:19,258 --> 00:58:20,589
Nothing else?

507
00:58:27,066 --> 00:58:27,998
Come on.

508
00:58:30,236 --> 00:58:32,704
- What is it?
- Come on.

509
00:58:49,021 --> 00:58:50,716
They're practicing witchcraft.

510
00:58:57,930 --> 00:58:59,158
Where are you going?

511
00:59:58,357 --> 00:59:59,517
Come to me.

512
01:00:00,025 --> 01:00:01,959
Hold on.

513
01:00:02,194 --> 01:00:03,491
Come to me.

514
01:00:06,465 --> 01:00:08,399
Darling.

515
01:00:09,368 --> 01:00:10,960
Take your hand away.

516
01:00:20,613 --> 01:00:23,207
There is an anthill.

517
01:00:23,282 --> 01:00:24,806
Anthill?

518
01:00:24,917 --> 01:00:25,941
Anthill.

519
01:00:26,652 --> 01:00:28,779
- Who is this?
- I don't know.

520
01:00:29,155 --> 01:00:30,679
Let's go.

521
01:02:11,790 --> 01:02:13,758
It seemed to me...

522
01:02:14,159 --> 01:02:15,956
...as if a black snake
was hiding himself.

523
01:02:16,061 --> 01:02:19,189
What are you doing?

524
01:02:21,200 --> 01:02:22,531
Let me go!

525
01:02:22,768 --> 01:02:24,963
We'll let you go.

526
01:02:25,070 --> 01:02:29,268
At dawn, we'll hang a stone around
your neck, to help you swim.

527
01:02:32,544 --> 01:02:36,878
Heaven's fire will consume you!
The Last Judgment awaits!

528
01:02:38,050 --> 01:02:40,780
Now we'll tie you to this cross...

529
01:02:42,354 --> 01:02:44,652
...like Jesus Christ.

530
01:02:46,191 --> 01:02:50,753
What are you doing, men?
You can't do this to me.

531
01:02:52,798 --> 01:02:55,323
This is a sin. At least
hang me upside-down.

532
01:02:55,935 --> 01:02:58,426
Men, brothers!

533
01:03:03,242 --> 01:03:08,305
Leave him here for the night,
unless he ascends again.

534
01:03:11,050 --> 01:03:12,915
He's not going anywhere.

535
01:03:26,966 --> 01:03:29,161
- And who is this?
- Marfa.

536
01:03:32,371 --> 01:03:37,001
Why did you want to be head
down? It would have been worse.

537
01:03:40,112 --> 01:03:42,910
Why did you threaten us
with fire from heaven?

538
01:03:44,383 --> 01:03:47,841
It is a sin to go naked
and do what you do.

539
01:03:50,289 --> 01:03:56,524
What sin? Tonight is for
lovemaking; is love a sin?

540
01:03:57,062 --> 01:03:59,826
Is it love to tie a man up like this?

541
01:04:01,433 --> 01:04:03,458
You might call the monks...

542
01:04:04,303 --> 01:04:06,533
...who would force us
to accept your faith.

543
01:04:06,872 --> 01:04:09,670
Do you think it's easy to live in fear?

544
01:04:10,342 --> 01:04:13,743
You live in fear because you
know no love but bestial love.

545
01:04:14,113 --> 01:04:18,174
Carnality without soul; but
love should be brotherly.

546
01:04:19,918 --> 01:04:22,478
Isn't all love the same? It's just love.

547
01:04:28,293 --> 01:04:29,282
What are you doing?

548
01:04:41,540 --> 01:04:42,837
Untie me.

549
01:07:55,133 --> 01:07:56,998
Why are you looking at me?

550
01:07:57,936 --> 01:07:59,301
Where were you?

551
01:08:04,509 --> 01:08:06,067
Thank God.

552
01:08:12,384 --> 01:08:14,579
Are these the people?

553
01:08:14,686 --> 01:08:17,746
No, these are strangers.
Don't you see it?

554
01:08:25,297 --> 01:08:27,765
There is some onion, if you want it.

555
01:08:36,375 --> 01:08:37,603
Where were you?

556
01:08:42,314 --> 01:08:46,307
These forests are impenetrable;
I'm all scratched.

557
01:08:48,487 --> 01:08:51,456
The local people like it.
They are accustomed to it.

558
01:08:52,090 --> 01:08:55,389
For people, everything
is a matter of custom.

559
01:08:56,161 --> 01:08:58,925
Old people don't need to think...

560
01:08:59,498 --> 01:09:02,990
...for their days pass
according to custom.

561
01:09:04,169 --> 01:09:09,698
But perhaps they consciously
enjoy the way the days drag on.

562
01:09:30,696 --> 01:09:33,187
- Couldn't you get here before?
- No. I couldn't.

563
01:09:34,800 --> 01:09:37,268
That is your sin, your
conscience, your prayers.

564
01:09:44,443 --> 01:09:46,468
Get him, and her!

565
01:10:04,463 --> 01:10:07,364
Why are they doing that?

566
01:10:07,999 --> 01:10:11,662
Because the accursed pagans
don't believe in one God.

567
01:10:12,204 --> 01:10:17,301
Don't look, Sergei. There
is nothing to look at.

568
01:10:18,977 --> 01:10:20,808
Let me go!

569
01:10:24,049 --> 01:10:25,641
- Let me go!
- You can't see that!

570
01:10:35,727 --> 01:10:38,628
Kick him so he shuts up!

571
01:10:45,070 --> 01:10:47,129
Go, go! Don't dawdle!

572
01:10:54,780 --> 01:10:57,408
Help, Fyodor! Help!

573
01:11:00,752 --> 01:11:01,810
Fyodor!

574
01:11:03,021 --> 01:11:05,990
Can't you deal with a woman?

575
01:11:07,192 --> 01:11:09,319
Stop!

576
01:11:10,061 --> 01:11:11,494
Hold her!

577
01:11:17,269 --> 01:11:19,134
Marfa, run!

578
01:11:19,204 --> 01:11:21,570
Catch her!

579
01:11:21,640 --> 01:11:24,507
- Where are you going?
- She will drown herself!

580
01:11:24,709 --> 01:11:28,270
Marfa! Run, Marfa!

581
01:11:33,318 --> 01:11:35,548
Swim, Marfa!

582
01:12:29,207 --> 01:12:34,509
THE LAST JUDGMENT
Summer 1 408

583
01:12:36,114 --> 01:12:37,138
Come here!

584
01:12:40,685 --> 01:12:42,619
He's just wasting materials.

585
01:12:42,854 --> 01:12:45,118
Who needs it?

586
01:12:47,692 --> 01:12:48,681
Foma!

587
01:12:49,194 --> 01:12:52,721
- What do you want?
- Can I go for a swim?

588
01:12:52,831 --> 01:12:55,766
- No, you can't.
- It's hot!

589
01:12:56,635 --> 01:12:58,432
Don't be lying. It's not.

590
01:12:58,737 --> 01:13:01,433
Maybe he's really hot. I'm hot too.

591
01:13:01,640 --> 01:13:03,767
Of course, you are
working and he is sitting.

592
01:13:03,875 --> 01:13:05,934
Let him go swim.

593
01:13:06,077 --> 01:13:07,977
Don't spoil him.

594
01:13:08,280 --> 01:13:09,611
Let him be sitting with everyone.

595
01:13:09,681 --> 01:13:11,615
You shut up!

596
01:13:11,783 --> 01:13:15,116
You sleep all day long like a log...

597
01:13:15,654 --> 01:13:19,021
...and you come down only
to eat and go to the bathroom.

598
01:13:19,524 --> 01:13:22,015
And have you found a job for me?

599
01:13:22,093 --> 01:13:24,926
- You have found what you wanted.
- So what?

600
01:13:26,064 --> 01:13:28,794
Since everyone is sitting here,
let Serezhka be sitting with us too.

601
01:13:28,900 --> 01:13:31,095
If you had let him go, he
would have been back already.

602
01:13:31,269 --> 01:13:33,260
Give him freedom...

603
01:13:33,338 --> 01:13:35,363
...and he will sit in the
water until he turns blue.

604
01:13:35,440 --> 01:13:37,374
He only thinks that it's hot...

605
01:13:37,442 --> 01:13:39,910
...and that's why he is whining.
- He's not whining, you are.

606
01:13:39,978 --> 01:13:40,910
It was me.

607
01:13:40,979 --> 01:13:43,880
I was the first to say
it's hot, and not Sergei.

608
01:13:43,949 --> 01:13:45,314
Why are you picking on Sergei?

609
01:13:46,785 --> 01:13:48,184
That's it!

610
01:13:48,587 --> 01:13:50,350
You want to go swimming, go!

611
01:13:50,755 --> 01:13:52,882
Go! Why are you sitting?

612
01:13:53,858 --> 01:13:55,826
Go, go!

613
01:13:56,928 --> 01:13:57,917
Here! You see?

614
01:13:58,530 --> 01:14:00,555
Wait! Wait!

615
01:14:03,874 --> 01:14:04,966
Where's Andrei?

616
01:14:05,976 --> 01:14:09,571
Not here? This is a
fine state of affairs.

617
01:14:14,685 --> 01:14:16,710
I was at our bishop's house just now.

618
01:14:18,889 --> 01:14:21,756
Such a fuss. Yelling!

619
01:14:22,860 --> 01:14:27,024
He was purple with rage.
" I've lost patience!" he cried.

620
01:14:27,364 --> 01:14:30,094
He meant you. All of you.

621
01:14:31,001 --> 01:14:34,300
" For two whole months," he said,
"everything has been ready.

622
01:14:34,371 --> 01:14:35,633
" But they haven't started yet.

623
01:14:35,706 --> 01:14:40,268
" Nothing is ready; they asked for
so much money, but do nothing.

624
01:14:40,811 --> 01:14:43,871
" None of them is working
and nothing is ready."

625
01:14:44,682 --> 01:14:47,344
Did you ask for a lot of money?

626
01:14:47,518 --> 01:14:49,110
How do I know?

627
01:14:49,386 --> 01:14:52,549
He said, " I don't care. Danil
Chorny or Andrei Rublev...

628
01:14:52,623 --> 01:14:54,557
"...it's all the same to me."

629
01:14:55,192 --> 01:14:58,093
" It's all the same."

630
01:14:58,729 --> 01:15:01,197
And he pulled a face like this.

631
01:15:04,535 --> 01:15:07,868
" What do I care
about Andrei Rublev?

632
01:15:10,407 --> 01:15:11,999
" By autumn," he says...

633
01:15:12,810 --> 01:15:15,301
"...I want the cathedral
painted, and that's that!"

634
01:15:16,313 --> 01:15:20,249
He's sent a courier with a
complaint to the Grand Prince.

635
01:15:21,719 --> 01:15:23,414
He's sent a courier
to the Grand Prince.

636
01:15:24,088 --> 01:15:26,579
It's a complaint about you, you know.

637
01:15:28,692 --> 01:15:31,354
You haven't started yet.

638
01:15:33,063 --> 01:15:38,057
You'd better hurry
up. Where's Andrei?

639
01:15:39,203 --> 01:15:41,103
He's gone somewhere again.

640
01:15:41,438 --> 01:15:43,463
Can't you start without him?

641
01:15:44,475 --> 01:15:46,238
Go on, start without him.

642
01:15:48,846 --> 01:15:51,576
Why are you smirking?
There are so many of you.

643
01:15:52,516 --> 01:15:55,314
If he can't make his mind
up, can't one of you?

644
01:15:55,386 --> 01:15:57,320
Two heads are better than one.

645
01:15:59,023 --> 01:16:00,388
Where is Andrei?

646
01:16:04,461 --> 01:16:06,088
I can't go on like that.

647
01:16:06,230 --> 01:16:07,925
Answer me: yes or no?

648
01:16:08,532 --> 01:16:11,831
Yes or no? Wasn't
everything decided in Moscow?

649
01:16:13,103 --> 01:16:18,097
To the smallest detail; the Prince
said everything was in order.

650
01:16:20,144 --> 01:16:25,241
What is not clear? What have we
been discussing for two months?

651
01:16:27,217 --> 01:16:30,050
Explain it to me. I may be
old, I may have lost my wits.

652
01:16:33,424 --> 01:16:35,790
The Last Judgment; either you
accept the task and paint it...

653
01:16:36,927 --> 01:16:39,020
...or you refuse the commission.

654
01:16:39,296 --> 01:16:42,959
And if we really refused?
If we went back, Danil?

655
01:16:43,333 --> 01:16:46,666
How shall I face people?
I should die of shame.

656
01:16:49,640 --> 01:16:52,074
We're wasting such good
time. This heat, no rain.

657
01:16:53,777 --> 01:16:57,008
We could have finished
the cupola and the columns.

658
01:16:58,315 --> 01:17:00,408
How wonderfully they
could have been done...

659
01:17:00,884 --> 01:17:02,613
...how brightly, and beautifully.

660
01:17:03,887 --> 01:17:05,548
On the right, the sinners...

661
01:17:06,423 --> 01:17:09,859
...boiling in pitch, painted
to make your flesh crawl.

662
01:17:12,296 --> 01:17:15,732
I have thought of a great devil,
with smoke from his nose and eyes.

663
01:17:16,500 --> 01:17:19,992
- It's not the smoke that matters.
- Then what matters?

664
01:17:20,104 --> 01:17:21,093
I don't know.

665
01:17:21,472 --> 01:17:24,032
- Why aren't you looking at me?
- Because I can't.

666
01:17:40,491 --> 01:17:45,121
I can't paint all that; it disgusts me.

667
01:17:47,364 --> 01:17:50,424
I don't want to terrify people.
Understand me, Danil.

668
01:17:52,436 --> 01:17:55,371
Collect yourself! Listen!
It's the Last Judgment!

669
01:17:55,973 --> 01:17:57,531
I didn't invent it.

670
01:17:57,608 --> 01:17:59,906
I can't do it. Do as
you will, but I can't.

671
01:18:00,043 --> 01:18:02,671
Why didn't you speak
earlier, in Moscow?

672
01:18:03,280 --> 01:18:04,838
You shouldn't have agreed.

673
01:18:07,151 --> 01:18:08,550
This is dishonest.

674
01:18:08,652 --> 01:18:11,644
I am what I am. You
couldn't teach me integrity.

675
01:18:28,639 --> 01:18:31,335
I don't know what to paint.

676
01:18:32,309 --> 01:18:33,867
What do you mean, you don't know?

677
01:18:35,145 --> 01:18:37,409
We were ordered to
paint the Last Judgment.

678
01:18:40,050 --> 01:18:41,711
You see...

679
01:18:43,053 --> 01:18:44,953
...I think it will be better...

680
01:18:45,255 --> 01:18:47,621
...if we don't paint the
Last Judgment at all.

681
01:18:49,826 --> 01:18:50,850
What do you mean?

682
01:18:52,963 --> 01:18:54,191
You know.

683
01:18:56,099 --> 01:18:57,396
I want...

684
01:19:06,276 --> 01:19:07,937
I don't want anything.

685
01:19:08,545 --> 01:19:10,775
- Nothing.
- That's it.

686
01:19:17,621 --> 01:19:19,589
Well, I'm leaving.

687
01:19:21,291 --> 01:19:23,987
This is no work for me.

688
01:19:24,995 --> 01:19:29,932
Thanks for your kindness and
your slaps; I learned something.

689
01:19:30,934 --> 01:19:33,232
But now I'm going to work for myself.

690
01:19:36,139 --> 01:19:38,471
They've asked me to
paint a church at Pafnutievo.

691
01:19:39,943 --> 01:19:41,740
Not a great honor,
but it's still an honor.

692
01:19:43,880 --> 01:19:46,576
I'm going to paint the Last Judgment.

693
01:19:48,719 --> 01:19:50,016
Who will come with me?

694
01:19:54,124 --> 01:19:55,648
Well, then, stay...

695
01:19:57,361 --> 01:19:59,329
...but don't complain later.

696
01:20:16,146 --> 01:20:17,807
When I was a child...

697
01:20:18,348 --> 01:20:23,650
...I spake as a child, I understood
as a child, I thought as a child...

698
01:20:24,354 --> 01:20:27,152
...but when I became a man,
I put away childish things.

699
01:20:27,958 --> 01:20:31,894
For now we see
through a glass, darkly...

700
01:20:32,429 --> 01:20:33,896
...but then face to face...

701
01:20:34,865 --> 01:20:36,389
...now I know in part...

702
01:20:36,933 --> 01:20:38,924
...but then shall I know...

703
01:20:39,002 --> 01:20:40,230
...even as also I am known.

704
01:20:41,338 --> 01:20:43,670
And now abideth...

705
01:20:44,107 --> 01:20:46,200
...faith, hope, and charity...

706
01:20:46,977 --> 01:20:48,945
...but the greatest of these is charity.

707
01:20:49,746 --> 01:20:53,443
Though I speak with the
tongues of men and of angels...

708
01:20:53,517 --> 01:20:54,848
...and have not charity...

709
01:20:55,218 --> 01:20:57,880
...I am become as sounding
brass, or a tinkling cymbal.

710
01:20:58,288 --> 01:20:59,846
And though I have
the gift of prophecy...

711
01:20:59,923 --> 01:21:01,914
...and understand all
mysteries, and all knowledge...

712
01:21:01,992 --> 01:21:06,554
...and though I have all faith, so
that I could remove mountains...

713
01:21:06,663 --> 01:21:08,893
...and have not charity, I am nothing.

714
01:21:09,266 --> 01:21:15,296
And though I bestow all
my goods to feed the poor...

715
01:21:16,506 --> 01:21:19,031
...and though I give my body to
be burned, and have not charity...

716
01:21:20,043 --> 01:21:22,568
...it profiteth me nothing.

717
01:21:22,779 --> 01:21:26,840
Charity suffereth long, and
is kind; charity envieth not...

718
01:21:26,917 --> 01:21:28,817
...charity vaunteth not
itself, is not puffed up...

719
01:21:30,087 --> 01:21:32,885
...doth not behave
itself unseemly...

720
01:21:32,956 --> 01:21:36,551
...seeketh not her own, is not
easily provoked, thinketh no evil...

721
01:21:38,762 --> 01:21:40,957
...rejoiceth not in iniquity,
but rejoiceth in the truth...

722
01:21:41,031 --> 01:21:44,467
...beareth all things...

723
01:21:44,568 --> 01:21:48,095
...believeth all things, hopeth
all things, endureth all things.

724
01:21:50,507 --> 01:21:52,702
Charity never faileth...

725
01:21:55,112 --> 01:21:57,342
...but whether there be
prophecies, they shall fail...

726
01:21:57,414 --> 01:21:59,348
...whether there be
tongues, they shall cease...

727
01:22:00,217 --> 01:22:02,378
...whether there be
knowledge, it shall vanish away.

728
01:22:03,587 --> 01:22:05,316
For we know in part...

729
01:22:07,657 --> 01:22:11,058
Princess, is that nice?

730
01:22:12,162 --> 01:22:14,255
It's sinful to splash milk.

731
01:22:15,265 --> 01:22:17,631
Such a naughtiness.

732
01:22:20,837 --> 01:22:24,568
- Why is it sinful?
- Because... wipe it off.

733
01:22:25,942 --> 01:22:28,240
But it will dry by itself in a minute.

734
01:22:29,379 --> 01:22:32,314
Let's walk by the stream.

735
01:22:35,952 --> 01:22:38,978
Let me go, Stepan, or I'll
send you to the stables.

736
01:22:43,460 --> 01:22:45,087
How do you like it?

737
01:22:46,663 --> 01:22:51,225
I couldn't imagine it
better. It's light, beautiful.

738
01:23:01,778 --> 01:23:03,006
It's light.

739
01:23:05,115 --> 01:23:09,575
Take her out. Her
nurses have spoiled her.

740
01:23:09,653 --> 01:23:11,120
I say!

741
01:23:11,188 --> 01:23:14,180
No one can build a
mansion better than us.

742
01:23:14,458 --> 01:23:16,619
Who could paint like that?

743
01:23:16,760 --> 01:23:17,749
Look at the carving.

744
01:23:17,828 --> 01:23:21,992
Only Mitiai can do this
directly, without tracing.

745
01:23:22,132 --> 01:23:24,100
It's like a bird singing.

746
01:23:25,735 --> 01:23:27,726
Look. Maybe it is like a bird singing.

747
01:23:29,840 --> 01:23:33,674
I don't care. I can sleep on the
hay. You are the Grand Prince.

748
01:23:33,844 --> 01:23:35,607
Don't you like it?

749
01:23:35,679 --> 01:23:38,147
I'll tell you this. It
should be repainted.

750
01:23:38,582 --> 01:23:41,210
Walls, ceiling, everything:
brighter, stronger colors.

751
01:23:43,887 --> 01:23:45,514
I've been in this trade for forty years.

752
01:23:45,655 --> 01:23:47,020
It's not the years that matter...

753
01:23:47,157 --> 01:23:49,625
...but your ability to glorify the
Grand Prince with your work.

754
01:23:49,693 --> 01:23:51,524
That's enough. Go.

755
01:23:53,964 --> 01:23:56,364
We won't redo anything.

756
01:23:56,666 --> 01:24:00,329
It's time to go. We have another job.

757
01:24:00,403 --> 01:24:02,268
They are waiting for us in Z venigorod.

758
01:24:03,173 --> 01:24:04,162
Where?

759
01:24:04,241 --> 01:24:07,574
At your brother's. They
have the stone already.

760
01:24:09,012 --> 01:24:11,378
A beautiful stone. Whiter than this.

761
01:24:12,349 --> 01:24:14,783
When your brother came at Easter...

762
01:24:15,585 --> 01:24:20,022
...we made a deal and he said: " Do
what you like, whatever the cost.

763
01:24:21,791 --> 01:24:25,454
" I'll tax the peasants more, just
build me the best mansion possible."

764
01:24:26,563 --> 01:24:28,929
Then go to Z venigorod.

765
01:24:33,169 --> 01:24:34,761
Here, I have brought it.

766
01:24:39,442 --> 01:24:42,468
When I looked at the
Prince, he became numb.

767
01:24:42,546 --> 01:24:47,643
- When I mentioned Z venigorod?
- Yes, he became paralyzed.

768
01:24:47,817 --> 01:24:50,809
He fears his brother will outshine him.

769
01:24:52,422 --> 01:24:55,391
- Who carved that?
- I did.

770
01:24:57,494 --> 01:24:59,359
Why didn't you set it in the wall?

771
01:25:00,196 --> 01:25:01,788
It didn't come out right.

772
01:25:02,365 --> 01:25:03,662
Pity; it's rather good.

773
01:25:05,368 --> 01:25:10,465
Everything crumbles: I told the Prince
to spare no expense on the stone.

774
01:25:11,174 --> 01:25:14,666
Maybe now he's sorry when
he heard about Z venigorod.

775
01:25:15,445 --> 01:25:17,413
I could have carved
beautiful things for him.

776
01:25:22,152 --> 01:25:25,485
Come on, you ass!

777
01:25:40,403 --> 01:25:41,700
Where's Stepan?

778
01:25:44,407 --> 01:25:46,602
Where did Stepan gallop to?

779
01:25:47,344 --> 01:25:49,505
He went to Z venigorod
with the others.

780
01:25:57,387 --> 01:25:59,617
I've dirtied my hands.

781
01:26:17,107 --> 01:26:21,009
We'll build another mansion just
as good for the Prince's brother.

782
01:26:21,945 --> 01:26:24,277
Will the stone be better there?

783
01:26:25,081 --> 01:26:26,480
Yes, it will.

784
01:26:27,617 --> 01:26:29,642
Look, the Captain of the Guard.

785
01:26:39,629 --> 01:26:40,994
Hold on, old man.

786
01:27:24,708 --> 01:27:28,235
You, ass! Help him! In the bushes!

787
01:27:39,222 --> 01:27:40,621
Where's my whip?

788
01:28:03,179 --> 01:28:06,148
Has anyone seen my whip?

789
01:28:08,118 --> 01:28:11,781
Damn. I've lost it. Have
you seen my whip, ass?

790
01:30:38,835 --> 01:30:40,803
- Seryoga.
- What?

791
01:30:41,704 --> 01:30:43,137
Read the Scriptures.

792
01:30:43,506 --> 01:30:44,495
From where?

793
